SVM with Kenrels

Support Vector Machine vc Logistic Rgression

n = number of features
m = number of training examples

if (n >> m: ex n = 10000, m = 1000)
Use LR or SVM without a kernel ("linear kernel")

if (n < m: ex n(1 - 1000), m (10 - 10000))
Use SVM with a gaussian kernel

if (n << m: ex n = 1 - 1000, m = 50000+)
Create/Add more features
Use LR or SVM without a kernel

Neural network work well for most of these settings, but may be slower to train.


Hypothesis: Given x, compute features f C Rn+1

kernel permet de retravailler sur les données dans une dimension supérieur
